<topic id='element_postcode.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Data Element: POSTCODE - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
         <b>Notes</b>:
              <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_postcode">POSTCODE</xref>
 is the same as attribute 
              <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_postcode">POSTCODE</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
For further information on 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_postcode">POSTCODES</xref>, see:        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
                     keyref="supporting_definition_nhs_postcode_directory">NHS Postcode Directory</xref>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
                     keyref="supporting_definition_contact_details">Contact Details</xref>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <xref href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/methodology/geography/ukgeographies/postalgeography"
                     scope="external"
                     format="html">Office for National Statistics website: Postal geography</xref>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_nhs_digital">NHS Digital</xref>
               <p>
 website at: 
                                <xref href="https://digital.nhs.uk/organisation-data-service/data-downloads/postcode-files"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html">ODS postcode files</xref>.                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
If a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_postcode">POSTCODE</xref>
 is not known, (for example, the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 has no fixed abode, the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 is an 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_overseas_visitor">Overseas Visitor</xref>
 etc.) the appropriate 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_organisation_data_service">Organisation Data Service</xref>
 pseudo 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_postcode">POSTCODE</xref>
 should be used.        </p>
      <p>
The pseudo 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_postcode">POSTCODES</xref>
 can be found on the 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_organisation_data_service">Organisation Data Service</xref>
 pages of the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nhs_digital">NHS Digital</xref>
 website at: 
              <xref href="https://digital.nhs.uk/services/organisation-data-service/data-downloads/office-for-national-statistics-data"
               scope="external"
               format="html">Office for National Statistics data</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
</body>
